# Retail Banking Budget Cycle Simulator
### 3-Year Strategic Plan | Macro Scenario Analysis | Staffing Forecast

> An interactive financial planning tool that simulates a retail bank division's full annual budget cycle — powered by real Federal Reserve macroeconomic data and deployed as a live web application.

**Live App:** https://retail-banking-budget-simulator-prakash.streamlit.app/

---

## What This Project Does

Most financial models live in static spreadsheets. This one is alive.

This simulator pulls real macroeconomic data directly from the Federal Reserve (FRED), uses it to define three distinct economic scenarios, and projects a full 3-year income statement, staffing forecast, and sensitivity analysis for a mid-size retail banking division — all updating in real time as you move the sliders.

It was built to demonstrate the exact planning skills used in a bank's annual budget cycle: building the base case, stress-testing assumptions, modeling headcount, and presenting results in a format senior management can actually use.

---

## Live Demo

Click any scenario and watch the entire financial plan update instantly:

- **Rising Rate** — Fed Funds climbing from 0% to 5.33% (calibrated to 2022–2023)
- **Flat Rate** — Stable mid-cycle environment (calibrated to 2019)
- **Falling Rate** — Emergency rate cuts and economic stress (calibrated to 2020)
- **Custom** — Set your own Fed Funds rate, loan growth, and GDP assumptions with live sliders

---

## Key Features

- **3-Year Income Statement Projections** — Net interest income, noninterest income, provisions, efficiency ratio, and net income across all three scenarios
- **Staffing Forecast Module** — FTE demand tied to loan volume with productivity benchmarks (18–24 FTE per $1B loans) and automated understaffing and overstaffing alerts
- **Sensitivity Analysis Tables** — One-way rate shock (±100bps) and volume shock (±5%) tables showing Year 3 net income impact with color-coded output
- **Interactive Visualizations** — Grouped bar charts, revenue waterfalls, staffing trend lines, and sensitivity heatmaps built in Plotly
- **Excel Export** — Download the full 3-year plan for any scenario as a formatted multi-sheet Excel workbook
- **Management Commentary** — Plain-English narrative generated dynamically for each scenario explaining the key drivers

---

## Data Sources

| Source | What It Provides |
|---|---|
| FRED — Federal Reserve Economic Data | Fed Funds Rate (FEDFUNDS), Real GDP (GDP), Unemployment Rate (UNRATE) — pulled live via API |
| BLS NAICS 5221 — Depository Credit Intermediation | FTE productivity benchmarks for staffing model |
| Simulated Division Financials | Industry-calibrated assumptions: NIM 2.8–3.4%, efficiency ratio 58–65%, charge-off rate 0.3–0.8% |

> **Disclaimer:** This is a financial modeling exercise using publicly available macroeconomic data and industry-standard banking ratios. It does not use or represent proprietary PNC Financial Services data.

