## Financial Planning Skills Demonstrated

- Annual budget cycle modeling from Year 0 actuals through 3-year projections
- Long-range strategic financial planning across multiple macro scenarios
- Staffing forecasts and workforce productivity analysis tied to business volume
- Macro scenario design calibrated to real Federal Reserve rate cycles
- Sensitivity analysis and stress testing for senior management presentations
- Operating leverage modeling and efficiency ratio management
- Translating complex financial models into accessible, interactive tools

---

## How the Model Works

**Step 1 — Real macro data in**
The app pulls live FRED data and uses historical rate cycles (2019, 2020, 2022–2023) to anchor three forward-looking scenarios rather than making up numbers.

**Step 2 — Scenario assumptions cascade through the P&L**
Each scenario drives a different NIM trajectory, loan growth rate, charge-off path, and fee income growth rate — all grounded in how retail banks actually behave in each rate environment.

**Step 3 — Staffing lags volume by one year**
The workforce model mirrors real planning cycles — hiring and training take time, so FTE demand in Year 1 is based on Year 0 loan volume.

**Step 4 — Sensitivity tables isolate each driver**
Rate shocks and volume shocks are applied independently so management can see exactly how much of the outcome is driven by rate versus volume.

